def: One who steals purses, or money from purses. Latimer. Shak.
An alloy of nicked with copper and zinc; German silver.
The fine shag or nap of velvet; a piece of velvet; velvetgoods.
The red-breasted or gray snipe (Macrorhamphus griseus); --called also brownback, and grayback.
In a manner not admitting of being convinced.
Mentioned before; already cited; aforementioned. Addison.
The light of the stars. [R.]The starshine lights upon our heads. R. L. Stevenson.
